<!--l. 3878--><p class="indent" >  Autumnal hues are splashed onto the trees; limp yellow leaves fall along with the
drops of rain splattering onto his umbrella. Dark brooding hangs in the sky, as he
walks into a suddenly altered unknown.
</p><!--l. 3882--><p class="indent" >  Dermot paces solemnly back towards the tram station, his mind spinning and
over-full with things to think about. Does he really believe what he has heard? Does
he care? Shouldn&#x2019;t it be someone else&#x2019;s job to ﬁgure this out? <span 
class="ptmri7t-x-x-109">I am just a programmer.</span>
<span 
class="ptmri7t-x-x-109">. .</span>
</p><!--l. 3887--><p class="indent" >  A skinny girl, in her mid twenties perhaps, is standing there waiting too. She has a
