</p><!--l. 6911--><p class="noindent" >*</p></div>
<!--l. 6914--><p class="indent" >  Released from the little library, he steps into the hall outside, right into the face of
someone having an animated conversation with a counterpart on the other end of a
mobile link. The man clearly signals irritation ‘<span 
class="ptmri7t-x-x-109">Watch it, buddy!</span>&#x2019; at the interruption
and waves, almost pushes, Den aside as he gesticulates. Den side-steps him and walks
back towards to central hall. The place seems to be emptying. People are collecting
coats.
</p><!--l. 6922--><p class="indent" >  He sees Cathy Kim. She looks pleased to see him and he mingles into the group she
is standing in. There is a smell of smoke again. The party seems to be breaking up, he
thinks.
</p><!--l. 6926--><p class="indent" >  A Brooklyn accent is waxing: “All civilizations conk out after a while. What makes
you think ours is any diﬀerent?” A large woman with her hair in the most elaborate
bun Den has ever seen.
</p><!--l. 6930--><p class="indent" >  “Well, say what you will about Reagan and Thatcher,” another is saying. “The
world had fallen down a well when they came on the scene. We were stuck. It wasn&#x2019;t
important what direction they took, whether they were moral or immoral: from a
purely theoretical viewpoint, they were the only two who could generate a strong

enough message to pull us out of that rut. Then once we were on a level playing ﬁeld
again, it was possible to change direction.”
</p><!--l. 6938--><p class="indent" >  “But are we really headed anywhere? Where is society going? From one rut to
another? Seems to me we&#x2019;re just grinding economic metal. We&#x2019;ve fallen into a new rut
of trading without vision. We have no direction. The days of future visions seem to be
dead.”
</p><!--l. 6943--><p class="indent" >  A Texas female voice. “Well, I don&#x2019;t know anything about your theory, but I do
know that their hard line was a welcome trait in my part of the world. How comforting
to know that there is a scientiﬁc explanation for it.”
</p><!--l. 6948--><p class="indent" >  She whispers to him. “What&#x2019;s going on?”
</p><!--l. 6950--><p class="indent" >  He is about to say that he would explain later; he remembers the General&#x2019;s warning.
“I was going to ask the same thing. Where is everyone going?”
</p><!--l. 6954--><p class="indent" >  “Home. Fires. We&#x2019;re being evacuated.”
</p><!--l. 6956--><p class="indent" >  Texas: “We must not accept a reduction of proﬁts that would deny us our very
ability to run the country. The privileged classes must prevail. Without the rich, there
is no one to inspire the poor. The class society is the only stable form of
society.”
</p><!--l. 6961--><p class="indent" >  “You know, I think I agree you are absolutely right. If these liberal intellectuals
argue for wealth to be spread too evenly, there will be no place for money to ﬂow.
Rivers ﬂow from great mountains, not over ﬂatlands. If we level the playing
ﬁeld too much we shall reach economic oblivion. It is the second law of
thermodynamics.”
</p><!--l. 6967--><p class="indent" >  Brooklyn: “The beginning and end of society. Control basic freedoms for the good
of basic freedoms. It is the paradox of society.”
</p><!--l. 6971--><p class="indent" >  Kim pulls him away from the group. “Come on, let&#x2019;s get out of here. The party&#x2019;s
over. We&#x2019;ve got what we came for.”
</p><!--l. 6974--><p class="indent" >  They step out into the hall. The blaze of sunshine entrance is gone.
</p><!--l. 6976--><p class="indent" >  “You have a coat?”
</p><!--l. 6978--><p class="indent" >  “I left a sweater in my car. you?”
</p><!--l. 6980--><p class="indent" >  She shakes her head. “Acclimatized native. I can sit with you?”
</p><!--l. 6982--><p class="indent" >  “Are you kidding?”
</p><!--l. 6984--><p class="indent" >  People are streaming out to the wardrobe to collect their belongings. Den Morris
and Cathy Kim weave through a tunnel of conversation.
</p><!--l. 6987--><p class="indent" >  “<span 
class="ptmri7t-x-x-109">The U.S cannot continue to foot the bill of this global economic policy. . .You</span>
<span 
class="ptmri7t-x-x-109">know, we tried consolidating our allies through the GATs treaty. The goddamn W.T.O..</span>
<span 
class="ptmri7t-x-x-109">It&#x2019;s a disgrace the way they treat America. . .America used to be a place people ran to</span>
<span 
class="ptmri7t-x-x-109">escape from the rest of the world. Now we are having to re-inﬁltrate every corner of</span>
<span 
class="ptmri7t-x-x-109">it.</span>”
</p><!--l. 6993--><p class="indent" >  “<span 
class="ptmri7t-x-x-109">Some say it is revenge. . .The demographics will kill us. It&#x2019;s the aged.</span>”
</p><!--l. 6996--><p class="indent" >  Don&#x2019;t listen.
</p><!--l. 6998--><p class="indent" >  Out into the thick haze of a darkened sky.
</p>
