something wrong with people like that, right? “So he was your boyfriend?” he
mutters, trying to sound as though he doesn&#x2019;t care.
</p><!--l. 16191--><p class="indent" >  “We used to fuck”

</p><!--l. 16193--><p class="indent" >  He nods, ﬁghting a bolt of panic, unnerved by a word which looms too
largely in his mind. He fumbles to continue his nonchalance. “So. . .what
