</p><!--l. 16197--><p class="indent" >  “He left me cause I was a bitch.” She says it with almost complete dispassion, an
even lack of emotion. She puﬀs on her cigarette. Dermot has hardly ever seen
a cigarette before, except in old movies. He is not quite sure what to say
now.
</p><!--l. 16202--><p class="indent" >  “Doesn&#x2019;t that make you sad? No regrets?”
</p><!--l. 16204--><p class="indent" >  She shrugs.
</p><!--l. 16206--><p class="indent" >  “So you need a new boyfriend then,” he jokes, ﬁshing for information.
</p><!--l. 16208--><p class="indent" >  She shrugs and inhales long and hard on the cigarette, wincing, almost as though in
