</p><!--l. 23114--><p class="indent" >  There is a sudden roar of enthusiasm from the table of football supporters.
</p><!--l. 23116--><p class="indent" >  “Hey-ho. Looks like the tribe is about to go hunting.”
</p><!--l. 23118--><p class="indent" >  Dermot looks uncomfortably at the table.
</p><!--l. 23120--><p class="indent" >  “Looks like a bug in your software, Dermot. I think they belong in a diﬀerent
game.”
</p><!--l. 23123--><p class="indent" >  “I wish,”
</p><!--l. 23125--><p class="indent" >  “You could go over and re-program them a little?”
</p><!--l. 23127--><p class="indent" >  “Avatars are easier to understand,” he mumbles and consults his mobile, checking
